rComments: Dr. Phillips is very encouraging; however, her lectures can get a bit dull. The class relies heavily on the textbook, and she assigns homework for every class. There are a lot of evaluations too. My issues are mostly with the course structure and not with Dr. Phillips.
She's super nice, and if you're having a problem she would be more than happy to help you out. There is homework though, and it counts towards your mark.

I am currently taking FSL305 and I hear she teaches FSL205 as well and I think she is a REALLY AMAZING French professor. I hear about the others, and in comparison, she is really good. Really easy to talk to, very passionate about French culture and the language She got emotional some times :'( . If you have her, DO NOT SWITCH OUT!
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: She is so nice! Had her for both FRE180 and FRE181, she's always there to help and she is good at explaining topics. Her tests are straightforward and help with showing you exactly where you need to improve.

Catherine Phillips is a down-to-earth great prof, her french is very clear -perfect for newbies to the language. She gives explanations for the TLF (Textes Littéraires Français) and genuinely cares about students' learning. She gets class participation where we get a chance to practice the language and participation marks. Would for sure recommend!
